<TITLE> NSC to make decision on Fatullah immediately </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 6 (bdnews24.com)  The National Sports Council will discuss with the Bangladesh Cricket Board the request of allotting the Fatullah Stadium, which was exclusively built for cricket, after the Bangladesh Football Federation sought its use. "We ourselves discussed the matter and now we will want to know the BCB's Fatullah-based schedules," NSC secretary Shafiq Anwar told bdnews24.com on Wednesday. Anwar said that the NSC had earlier allotted the Fatullah Stadium for cricket, and they would make their decision as soon as possible as the Senior Division Football League was scheduled to start from June 1. The BFF on Tuesday requested the NSC to allot them the Fatullah Cricket Stadium for three months for its busy schedules, which include the Senior Division Football League, School Girls football and Women's Corporate Football. The BCB has already reacted sharply and said that there was hardly any logic to play football in a purpose-built cricket stadium. bd
